28","1317":"1317","1306":"1306","Bordeaux, Guyenne, France":"Bordeaux, Guyenne, Frankrig","Halstead, Essex, England":"Halstead, Essex, England","Essex, England":"Essex, England","Colchester, Essex, England":"Colchester, Essex, England"},"nl":{"about 1281–1349":"circa 1281–1349","1281–1349":"1281–1349","1290–1329":"1290–1329","1306–1348":"1306–1348","1312–Male":"1312–Overleden","1245–1285":"1245–1285","1247–Female":"1247–Overleden","about 1281":"circa 1281","1285":"1285","about 20 August 1348":"circa 20 augustus 1348","1281":"1281","1290":"1290","1349":"1349","1337":"1337","1315":"1315","1348":"1348","about 1329":"circa 1329","1247":"1247","about 1305":"circa 1305","after 1306":"na 1306","1312":"1312","1245":"1245","1453":"1453","about 1312":"circa 1312","1329":"1329","about 1285":"circa 1285","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","1306":"1306","Bordeaux, Guyenne, France":"Bordeaux, Guyenne, Frankrijk","Halstead, Essex, England":"Halstead, Essex, England","Essex, England":"Essex, England","Colchester, Essex, England":"Colchester, Essex, England"},"en":{"about 1281–1349":"about 1281–1349","1281–1349":"1281–1349","1290–1329":"1290–1329","1306–1348":"1306–1348","1312–Male":"1312–Deceased","1245–1285":"1245–1285","1247–Female":"1247–Deceased","about 1281":"about 1281","1285":"1285","about 20 August 1348":"about 20 August 1348","1281":"1281","1290":"1290","1349":"1349","1337":"1337","1315":"1315","1348":"1348","about 1329":"about 1329","1247":"1247","about 1305":"about 1305","after 1306":"after 1306","1312":"1312","1245":"1245","1453":"1453","about 1312":"about 1312","1329":"1329","about 1285":"about 1285","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","1306":"1306","Bordeaux, Guyenne, France":"Bordeaux, Guyenne, France","Halstead, Essex, England":"Halstead, Essex, England","Essex, England":"Essex, England","Colchester, Essex, England":"Colchester, Essex, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Colchester","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["English: locative name from Colchester (Essex)."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Helen","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["vernacular form of the name (Greek <i>Hēlēnē</i>) borne in classical legend by a famous beauty, wife of Menelaus, whose seizure by the Trojan prince Paris sparked off the Trojan War. Her name is of uncertain origin; it may be connected with a word meaning ‘ray’ or ‘sunbeam’ compare Greek <i>hēlios</i> ‘sun’. It has sometimes been taken as connected with the Greek word meaning ‘Greek’, <i>Hellēn</i>, but this is doubtful. In the early Christian period the name was borne by the mother of the Emperor Constantine, who is now usually known by the Latin version of her name, <i>Helena</i>. She is credited with having found the True Cross in Jerusalem. She was born in about  248 , probably in Bithynia. However, in medieval England it was believed that she had been born in Britain, which greatly increased the popularity of the name there."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705190,"age":9,"year":"1290","julianDay":2192224,"title":"Jews Expelled From England","description":"After years of anti-Semitic behavior, King Edward I expelled Jews from England in 1290.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705191,"age":34,"year":"1315","toYear":"1317","julianDay":2201354,"title":"Famine Strikes Europe","description":"A famine caused by cold winters and wet summers across Europe caused millions to die due to starvation. Desperation from hunger caused high levels of crime, stampedes in bread lines in London, infanticide, and even cannibalism throughout Europe.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705192,"age":47,"year":"1328","julianDay":2206102,"title":"First War of Scottish Independence","description":"The First War of Scottish Independence began after England invaded Scotland in 1296. The Treaty of Edinburgh was signed in 1328 which declared peace between the two kingdoms and brought the war to an end.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705193,"age":56,"year":"1337","toYear":"1453","julianDay":2209390,"title":"The Hundred Years' War","description":"The Hundred Years' War between France and England was largely due to the question of legitimate succession to the French crown.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Helen Colchester was born about 1281, in Halstead, Essex, England, her father, Walter de Colchester, was 38 and her mother, Joan Munchensey, was 36. She married John Bourchier about 1305, in Colchester, Essex, England. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. She died in 1349, in her hometown, at the age of 69, and was buried in Halstead, Essex, England."},"et":{"about 1281–1349":"umbes 1281–1349","1281–1349":"1281–1349","1290–1329":"1290–1329","1306–1348":"1306–1348","1312–Male":"1312–Surnud","1245–1285":"1245–1285","1247–Female":"1247–Surnud","about 1281":"umbes 1281","1285":"1285","about 20 August 1348":"umbes 20. august 1348","1281":"1281","1290":"1290","1349":"1349","1337":"1337","1315":"1315","1348":"1348","about 1329":"umbes 1329","1247":"1247","about 1305":"umbes 1305","after 1306":"pärast 1306","1312":"1312","1245":"1245","1453":"1453","about 1312":"umbes 1312","1329":"1329","about 1285":"umbes 1285","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","1306":"1306","Bordeaux, Guyenne, France":"Bordeaux, Guyenne, Prantsusmaa","Halstead, Essex, England":"Halstead, Essex, England","Essex, England":"Essex, England","Colchester, Essex, England":"Colchester, Essex, England"},"fi":{"about 1281–1349":"noin 1281–1349","1281–1349":"1281–1349","1290–1329":"1290–1329","1306–1348":"1306–1348","1312–Male":"1312–Kuollut","1245–1285":"1245–1285","1247–Female":"1247–Kuollut","about 1281":"noin 1281","1285":"1285","about 20 August 1348":"noin 20. elokuuta 1348","1281":"1281","1290":"1290","1349":"1349","1337":"1337","1315":"1315","1348":"1348","about 1329":"noin 1329","1247":"1247","about 1305":"noin 1305","after 1306":"1306 jälkeen","1312"